# Robots (`**/robots.ts`)

## Sitemap link
- **`sitemap`** must be an **absolute** URL pointing at the deployed sitemap (often `https://www.example.com/sitemap.xml`), aligned with **`metadataBase`** and **`sitemap.ts`** output.

## Host and environment
- If **`baseUrl`** is derived from **`x-forwarded-host`** / **`host`**, confirm **preview** and **production** hosts do not accidentally publish wrong origins or block crawlers on prod.
- Staging: often **`Disallow: /`** or auth wall—do not copy staging robots to production without review.

## Rules blocks
- **`allow`** / **`disallow`** paths must match real **`app`** routes; avoid typos that block CSS or Next static assets unintentionally.
- When listing **AI / LLM** user agents, keep lists maintainable and match current product policy.

## Consistency
- If certain routes use **`noindex`** in metadata, robots rules should not **allow** crawling in a way that contradicts the intended indexing story without a documented reason.
